MEMENTO

Problem:
Need to save and restore an object’s previous state without exposing its internals.
like implementing undo on a word sheet

Core idea:
Store snapshots of state in separate memento objects.

Roles:
Originator
Memento    class to snapshot
Caretaker  class to store snapshots on list

When not to use:
When state is large, restoration is rarely needed, or snapshotting is too expensive.
in this situation we use command pattern (break obj to it's commands
                                          and use memento on each commands)

