ITERATOR

Problem:
Need to traverse a collection without exposing its internal structure.
we have an iterable obj but we don't know he is list,map,...

Core idea:
Move traversal logic into a separate iterator object.

Roles:
Iterator,
ConcreteIterator,  inner class that return iterator obj
Aggregate / Collection

When not to use:
When simple loops are enough or traversal logic is trivial.

