Command

Problem:
Need to turn requests into objects so they can be queued, logged, undone, or executed later.
like button action

Core idea:
Wrap an action and its receiver inside a command object.

Roles:
Command,            an Interface that defines commands
ConcreteCommand,    each commands, like button to addCustomer/ button to remove Customer
Invoker,
Receiver,           where we have actual code (like customerService that can add customer)
Client

When not to use:
When actions are very simple and objectifying them adds too much boilerplate.

