Strategy

Problem:
Need different interchangeable algorithms for the same task.
like different algorithms to compress videos!
it's like state (we have so many if/else), but context class has not different states!

Core idea:
Encapsulate each algorithm behind a common interface.

Roles:
Strategy,           each purpose has his interface (an interface to compress videos)
ConcreteStrategy,   we have multiple class to implement each algorithm (jpg/png/...)
Context             the class use these strategies (like ImageStorage)

When not to use:
When there are only one or two simple variants and extra abstraction is unnecessary.

-------------------------------------------
Template Method

Problem:
Need a fixed algorithm structure with some customizable steps.
like store log on every customer operations (transfer money/ generate report/...)

Core idea:
Define the skeleton in a base class and let subclasses override specific steps.

Roles:
AbstractClass,  like Task class (all customer operations is kind of task)
ConcreteClass

When not to use:
When inheritance is not wanted or behavior should vary at runtime.

