Visitor

Problem:
Need to add new operations to a group of object types without changing their classes.
(like we have an Interface, if we want to add new method, we should modify all classes
 we want to prevent this)

Core idea:
Move the operation into a visitor object and let each element accept it.
instead we have multiple method on our base Interface, we make it singular (accept all operations by polymorphism)
we create another interface to cover these operations by overloading (visitor)

Roles:
Visitor,           (an Interface that has some overload method to cover all classes)
ConcreteVisitor,   (class that implement overload methods (visit other classes))
Element,           (the main class like HtmlDocument )
ConcreteElement

When not to use:
When the element hierarchy changes often, because every new element affects all visitors.
(we have stable object structure)